  <span id="freeText15529535719222571117" style="display:none">Really charming little fairy-taleish stories about well-born once-upon-a-time people and their relationship problems. The most striking thing to a modern reader is the adultery thing. There's not really a taboo around it, though a lot of the women have very jealous husbands who aren't keen on it. One lady makes her lover swear he believes in God before she'll sleep with him. It's like they're enthusiastic about this Christianity thing but haven't quite got the hang of it.<br /><br />This really delivers on the picturesque mediaeval details. It's a very <i>pretty</i> book.</span>
