<div id="review_3863052551" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3863052551" />
    <a title="Elijah McLellan" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/124159112-elijah-mclellan"><img alt="Elijah McLellan" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1608389834p2/124159112.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3863052551?book_show_action=true">May 20, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Elijah McLellan" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Elijah McLellan" href="/user/show/124159112-elijah-mclellan">Elijah McLellan</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3863052551" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1107526077911872366">I enjoyed the Lais of Marie de France... They are certainly no book upon which one ought to base their moral decisions, however, it is an interesting view into the early developments of Courtly Love. As well, it is intriguing to see her approach some Arthurian themes and even a little snippet from the story of Tristan and Isolde.</span>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

